  "text": "In recent years, superconductors have once again attracted a lot of attention because superconductor-based quantum bits (qubits) are promising candidates as basic elements of quantum computing systems [CITATION_1] - [CITATION_2] . Although there are several types of superconducting qubits, such as charge, flux, phase, and transmon qubits, the basic element in common is the Josephson junctions. Superconducting quantum annealers also comprise arrays of direct-current Manuscript received October 13, 2017 . Manuscript revised December 26, 2017 . † The author is with NICT Advanced ICT Research Institute, Kobe-shi, 651-2492 Japan.",
